1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about nonhomologous end joining than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:11,600
Nonhomologous end joining is a crucial DNA repair process that fixes breaks without needing a template.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,400
Imagine your DNA is like a book.

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,600
Sometimes, pages tear.

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:20,000
Nonhomologous end joining just glues them back, but not always perfectly.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,600
This method is fast but can lead to mutations.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:28,400
It's like rushing to fix that page without reading what was lost.

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:35,600
Understanding this process helps scientists grasp cancer development and genetic disorders, revealing how our cells adapt under pressure.

9
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,400
Curious about how your body repairs itself?

10
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,800
Hit subscribe for more science insights!
